            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Ahoy, matey! Arr! — Good ta see ye aboard.\n\nFer tellin' ye what to wear outside today, I need yer port o' call or the weather where ye be. If ye can't give that, here be quick dressin' charts dependin' on the feel o' the day:\n\n- Bitter cold (below ~40°F / <4°C): heavy coat or parka, warm layers, wool hat, gloves, scarf, insulated boots.  \n- Chilly (40–55°F / 4–13°C): medium coat or puffer vest, sweater, long pants, closed shoes.  \n- Cool to mild (55–70°F / 13–21°C): light jacket or cardigan, long-sleeve or tee, jeans or chinos.  \n- Warm (70–80°F / 21–27°C): short sleeves, light trousers or shorts, breathable fabrics, sun hat if sunny.  \n- Hot (above ~80°F / >27°C): shorts, breathable cotton or linen, sun protection, stay hydrated.\n\nIf it's rainin' or windy: bring a waterproof jacket or windbreaker and an umbrella; waterproof shoes be a wise choice. If ye'll be doin' heavy walkin' or adventurin': wear comfortable, supportive shoes. For fancy ports o' call, swap in smarter layers and shoes.\n\nTell me yer city or current temp and what ye'll be doin' today, and I'll give ye a tailored outfit, arr!",
